  "base_commit": "592dba14891e21ed31eaefcb2ccd7714ff984f67",
  "pr_number": 14782,
  "issue_number": 14781,
  "issue_title": "[Bug]: Retrieval endpoints trust caller-supplied `tenant_rerank_id` and load rerank models by global ID without tenant authorization",
  "issue_body": "### Self Checks\n\n- [x] I have searched for existing issues [search for existing issues](https://github.com/infiniflow/ragflow/issues), including closed ones.\n- [x] I confirm that I am using English to submit this report ([Language Policy](https://github.com/infiniflow/ragflow/issues/5910)).\n- [x] Non-english title submitions will be closed directly ( \u975e\u82f1\u6587\u6807\u9898\u7684\u63d0\u4ea4\u5c06\u4f1a\u88ab\u76f4\u63a5\u5173\u95ed ) ([Language Policy](https://github.com/infiniflow/ragflow/issues/5910)).\n- [x] Please do not modify this template :) and fill in all the required fields.\n\n### RAGFlow workspace code commit ID\n\n592dba14891e21ed31eaefcb2ccd7714ff984f67\n\n### RAGFlow image version\n\ninfiniflow/ragflow:v0.25.2\n\n### Other environment information\n\n```Markdown\n- Browser: N/A (backend/API issue)\n- OS: N/A\n```\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nWhen `tenant_rerank_id` is provided, the code resolves the rerank model via a global ID lookup (`get_model_config_by_id(...)`) with no tenant authorization check before building `LLMBundle(...)`.\n\nThis appears to allow model-selection by raw database ID rather than by tenant-scoped authorization.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nCaller-supplied tenant model IDs should be rejected unless the model belongs to the authenticated tenant, or to the dataset owner tenant if cross-tenant team sharing is explicitly supported for rerank models.\n\nRetrieval should use only tenant-authorized rerank models, similar to the safer `rerank_id -> get_model_config_by_type_and_name(...)` path.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```Markdown\n1.\n   Prepare two tenants, A and B. Tenant A must have a rerank model configured in `TenantLLM`. Obtain or infer A's numeric `tenant_rerank_id`.\n\n2.\n   Authenticate as tenant B and call a retrieval endpoint that accepts `tenant_rerank_id`, for example `POST /api/v1/retrieval` or `POST /api/v1/searchbots/retrieval_test`, using a dataset that tenant B is allowed to access.\n\n3.\n   Set `tenant_rerank_id` in the request body to tenant A's model id and submit the retrieval request.\n```\n\n### Additional information\n\nSome retrieval endpoints accept `tenant_rerank_id` directly from the request and resolve it with `get_model_config_by_id(...)`. That helper performs a global lookup by `TenantLLM.id` and returns decoded model configuration without checking whether the model belongs to the authenticated tenant or the dataset owner tenant.\n\nThis is important because the affected endpoints otherwise do validate dataset access, so the rerank-model path becomes an authorization bypass for model selection. A caller who knows or can guess another tenant's `tenant_rerank_id` may be able to run retrieval using a rerank model config they do not own.\n\nConfirmed call sites include:\n\n- `api/apps/sdk/doc.py` (`POST /api/v1/retrieval`)\n- `api/apps/sdk/session.py` (`POST /api/v1/searchbots/retrieval_test`)\n- `api/apps/services/dataset_api_service.py` (shared retrieval service path)\n\nThe common sink is:\n\n- `api/db/joint_services/tenant_model_service.py:get_model_config_by_id()`\n\nwhich calls `TenantLLMService.get_by_id(...)` and returns the model config, but does not verify tenant ownership / accessibility before use.",
  "merged_at": "2026-05-13T11:53:09.000Z",
